procedures.name: Blood Sampling
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), and clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation).

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, pregnancy testing, drug screening, and 24-hour collection for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

code.decode: Volume measurement for timed collection, each

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems. Height, weight, and BMI are also measured.

code.decode: Office or other outpatient visit for the evaluation and management of a new patient

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and other clinically significant findings.

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Clinical Safety Laboratory Assessments
procedures.label: Safety Labs
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis of blood samples, including serum chemistry, hematology, and coagulation panels.

procedures.name: Urinalysis
procedures.label: Urinalysis
procedures.description: Analysis of urine samples for safety assessment.

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent for bilirubin, glucose, hemoglobin, ketones, leukocytes, nitrite, pH, protein, specific gravity, urobilinogen, any number of these constituents; automated, with microscopy

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine and/or serum pregnancy tests for females of childbearing potential.

code.decode: Urine pregnancy test, by visual color comparison methods

procedures.name: Alcohol Test
procedures.label: Alcohol Test
procedures.description: Test to screen for alcohol use.

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.description: Test to screen for disallowed drug use.

procedures.name: HIV, Hepatitis B and C Screen
procedures.label: Viral Screen
procedures.description: Screening for Human Immunodeficiency Virus, Hepatitis B, and Hepatitis C.

procedures.name: Bowel and Urine Monitoring
procedures.label: Bowel/Urine Monitoring
procedures.description: Monitoring of urination and bowel movements, including menstruation checks for women.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure and Heart Rate Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Device
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Catheter
medicalDevices.label: IV Catheter
medicalDevices.description: A catheter may be placed for venous access to minimize needle sticks, not to be left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Laboratory equipment used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
